<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4773074>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 5. Edentulous anuran maxillae from the middle – late Campanian (Judithian) of Alberta, Canada and Utah, USA. All images are photographs and depict specimens lightly dusted with ammonium chloride to enhance details and texture. Images at different magnifications; see corresponding scale bars. a–f – Tyrrellbatrachus brinkmani GARDNER, 2015, all from basal part of Dinosaur Park Formation, Dinosaur Provincial Park,Alberta: a, b – incomplete right maxilla, TMP 1985.066.0035 (holotype), in labial (a) and lingual (b) views, from TMP locality L0404; c, d – incomplete right maxilla, TMP 1986.033.0033, in labial (c) and lingual (d) views, from TMP locality L0031; e, f – incomplete left maxilla, TMP 1986.214.0032, in labial (e) and lingual (f) views, from TMP locality L0051. g, h – Theatonius n. sp., nearly complete left maxilla, OMNH 67082, in labial (g) and lingual (h) views, from Kaiparowits Formation, OMNH locality V6, Utah." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4773074/files/figure.png" .
